page.title: 12SEISDON EGG PACKING STATION
page.content: This is the largest and most noticeable man-made feature in the district and was first built in the teeth of strong local opposition. With the passage of time people have become more resigned but it is still unpopular because of the unpleasant smells produced and the eye-sore it constitutes. It covers a sizeable plot and there are a number of low sheds placed round a tall silo where grain is stored and ground for poultry feed. Because of the flat landscape the silo tower is visible over a wide area.
